## The 30-second cheatsheet

| Concern | Pattern | Don't do |
|---|---|---|
| Per-policy reconciled summary | Fetch `/api/accounting/statements/by-policy/:pid?audience=agent` + render `<StatementPaymentCard>` | Sum `row.totalAmountCents` and `row.paidAmountCents` across categories |
| Per-row "is paid?" badge | Check `wasClientPaidDirectly` / `hasClientDirectSubmitted` BEFORE comparing paid vs total | Map `status==='pending'` â†’ "UNPAID" without consulting those flags |
| Group total / outstanding in a list banner | Either fetch the statement OR explicitly label as "Document totals (not reconciled)" | Show a naive sum as if it's the policy total |
| Orphan rows (no `policyId`) | Hide by default; never include in group reconciliation | Show as UNPAID receivables that need attention |
| New dashboard surface showing per-policy state | Point at the statement endpoint OR the agent-detail summary card | Reinvent the math |

## Bedrock rule (from `insurance-platform-architecture.mdc`)

> NEVER sum client + agent payments as if they're separate debts â€”
> they settle ONE policy obligation.
>
> Either payer settling their amount = policy fully paid. They are
> alternative paths, NOT additive debts.

If anything above is unclear, the skill has the full contract, the
data model in 5 lines, the badge priority order, the implementation
patterns, the "what NOT to do" list, and a verification recipe (open
the four canonical surfaces for the same policy and confirm the
numbers match).
